  "local_port": 53876,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I filter out US election news in my Quora feed?",
  "response": "Filtering out specific topics like US election news from your Quora feed can help tailor your experience to your preferences. While Quora doesn't offer a direct \"exclude\" feature, you can achieve this by managing the topics you follow and using other available settings. Here's how you can do it:\n\n### 1. **Unfollow Relevant Topics**\n\nUS election news is typically associated with specific topics. By unfollowing these topics, related content will no longer appear in your feed.\n\n- **Identify Relevant Topics:**\n  - **Politics**\n  - **United States Politics**\n  - **Elections**\n  - **US Presidential Elections**\n  - **Political Commentary**\n\n- **Steps to Unfollow Topics:**\n  1. **Navigate to the Topic Page:**\n     - Use the search bar at the top of Quora to find each relevant topic (e.g., \"United States Politics\").\n  2. **Unfollow the Topic:**\n     - On the topic page, click the **\"Following\"** button. It will change to **\"Follow\"**, indicating you've unfollowed the topic.\n  3. **Repeat for All Relevant Topics:**\n     - Ensure you've unfollowed all topics related to US elections to minimize related content in your feed.\n\n### 2. **Adjust Your Content Preferences**\n\nQuora allows you to manage your preferences to better control the content you see.\n\n- **Steps to Adjust Preferences:**\n  1. **Go to Settings:**\n     - Click on your profile picture in the top-right corner and select **\"Settings\"** from the dropdown menu.\n  2. **Navigate to \"Customize Your Interests\":**\n     - Look for sections like **\"Settings\"** > **\"Manage Topics\"** or **\"Customize Your Interests\"**.\n  3. **Modify Your Interests:**\n     - Remove or reduce interests related to politics and elections.\n  4. **Save Changes:**\n     - Ensure you save or apply any changes made to update your feed accordingly.\n\n### 3. **Use the \"Hide\" Feature on Specific Posts**\n\nIf you come across specific posts related to US elections that you don't want to see:\n\n- **Steps to Hide Posts:**\n  1. **Find the Post:**\n     - In your feed, locate a post related to US elections.\n  2. **Hide the Post:**\n     - Click on the three dots (**\"\u2026\"**) at the top-right corner of the post.\n     - Select **\"Hide\"** or **\"Hide all from [Topic/User]\"** to prevent similar content from appearing.\n\n### 4. **Block Specific Users or Content**\n\nIf certain users consistently post US election content:\n\n- **Steps to Block Users:**\n  1. **Visit the User's Profile:**\n     - Click on the user's name to go to their profile.\n  2. **Block the User:**\n     - Click on the three dots (**\"\u2026\"**) near their profile picture.\n     - Select **\"Block\"** to prevent their content from appearing in your feed.\n\n### 5. **Provide Feedback to Quora**\n\nIf you find that existing options don't fully meet your needs, consider providing feedback to Quora:\n\n- **Steps to Provide Feedback:**\n  1. **Go to Settings or Help:**\n     - Access the **\"Help\"** or **\"Feedback\"** section from the dropdown menu under your profile picture.\n  2. **Submit Your Request:**\n     - Explain that you'd like more granular control over the topics you see, such as excluding specific news categories like US elections.\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n\n- **Regularly Review Followed Topics:**\n  Periodically check the topics you follow to ensure they align with your current interests.\n  \n- **Engage with Preferred Content:**\n  The more you engage with topics you\u2019re interested in, the more Quora's algorithm will tailor your feed to prioritize those interests over others.\n\nBy following these steps, you can significantly reduce or eliminate US election news from your Quora feed, creating a more personalized and enjoyable experience.",
